The paper deals with problems related to partitioning geometric sets in the plane, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of balanced subsets is also related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of Jordan curves, which is a topic in topology and geometry (cs.GT). Finally, the paper uses certain constraints on a set of points in the integer lattice, which could be related to computational number theory (cs.MS).
